There are two main approaches to check if strings are anagrams: APPROACH 1: Sorting (O(n log n)) - Sort both strings and compare if they're equal. Simple but slower. APPROACH 2: Hash Map / Character Count (O(n)) - Count frequency of each character and compare frequencies. Faster but more code. WHICH IS BETTER? Hash map is O(n) vs sorting O(n log n), but sorting is simpler to code. For small strings, both work fine!

// APPROACH 1: Sorting (O(n log n))
let sortedS = s.split('').sort().join('');
let sortedT = t.split('').sort().join('');
return sortedS === sortedT;

// APPROACH 2: Hash Map (O(n))
let count = {};
for (let char of s) {
  count[char] = (count[char] || 0) + 1;
}
for (let char of t) {
  count[char] = (count[char] || 0) - 1;
}
return Object.values(count).every(val => val === 0);

